## Security ‚Äî Non-Negotiable
- Supabase RLS is DISABLED on all tables by design ‚Äî all DB access via `service_role` key in Fastify only
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` is server-side env only ‚Äî never in Vercel env vars, never in frontend bundle
- `@supabase/supabase-js` in frontend: Google OAuth redirect only ‚Äî never direct DB access
- `anon` key: not used ‚Äî not in frontend bundle
- JWT access token stored in-memory client-side ‚Äî never `localStorage`, never `sessionStorage`
- Refresh token set as `httpOnly` cookie by server ‚Äî never by client code
- `apple_sub` column: reserved for native app ‚Äî return `501 NOT_IMPLEMENTED` on web MVP

## Database Access
- All DB queries via `src/shared/db.ts` Supabase client with `service_role` key
- Never import Supabase client in route files ‚Äî use service modules only
- Row ownership enforced by `auth-guard.ts` middleware + explicit `user_id` checks in every query
- Never skip `user_id` filter on any user-data table ‚Äî every query must be scoped to the authenticated user
- After every Supabase MCP `apply_migration` call: write the same SQL to `migrations/YYYYMMDDHHmmss_description.sql` ‚Äî remote DB and local repo must never drift

## API Conventions
- URL pattern: `/api/v1/{resource}[/{id}][/{action}]`
- Correct: `/api/v1/checkins`, `/api/v1/sessions/:id/complete`
- Wrong: `/api/v1/generateProtocol`, `/api/v1/getUserProgress`
- All successful responses: `{ success: true, data: T, meta?: {...} }`
- All error responses: `{ success: false, code: 'SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE', message: string, details?: object }`
- Never expose raw database errors to client ‚Äî always normalize to standard error shape
- Error codes from consolidated registry in tech spec Section 1.4 ‚Äî never invent new codes mid-build

## Auth
- Anonymous session header: `Authorization: Anonymous <anonymous_id>`
- Claimed session header: `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>`
- JWT TTL: 15 minutes access / 7 days refresh (httpOnly cookie `fw_refresh`)
- `auth-guard.ts` validates both anonymous and claimed sessions ‚Äî apply to all protected routes
- Rate limits enforced in `rate-limit.ts`: login 10/15min, register 5/1h, forgot-password 3/1h

## LLM Usage (Fastify backend only)
- Default to SQL and rule-based templates for all deterministic logic
- LLM calls approved only for:
  - `symptom-map.service.ts` ‚Äî symptom text ‚Üí condition mapping (Claude Haiku, target < 400ms)
  - `protocol.service.ts` ‚Äî first protocol assignment and adaptation (Claude Sonnet for assignment, Haiku for check-in responses)
  - `checkin.service.ts` ‚Äî daily check-in AI response generation (Claude Haiku, target < 1.5s P95)
- Monthly inference cost ceiling: $60/month ‚Äî log token usage per call in production
- All other logic (scheduling, notification dispatch, progress calculation, phase gate): SQL or templates only

## Third-Party SDK Wrapper Rule
- Import `@payos/node` only in `src/modules/billing/billing.service.ts` ‚Äî never in routes, components, or hooks
- Import Resend SDK only in `src/shared/email.ts`
- Import VAPID/web-push only in `src/modules/notifications/vapid.config.ts`
- Import Claude SDK only in `src/modules/protocol-engine/ai-provider.ts`
- Never import third-party SDKs directly in route handlers

## PayOS Rules
- Two separate flows ‚Äî never merge:
  - Desktop: QR code generation ‚Üí poll `GET /api/v1/billing/payment-status/:orderId` every 3s
  - Mobile: redirect to PayOS URL ‚Üí return via `GET /api/v1/billing/payos-return`
- PayOS credentials (`PAYOS_CLIENT_ID`, `PAYOS_API_KEY`, `PAYOS_CHECKSUM_KEY`): server-side only ‚Äî never in Vercel
- Payment confirmation must be verified server-side via webhook ‚Äî never trust client-side payment status
- Webhook URL: `https://api.fitwell.vn/api/v1/billing/payos-webhook` ‚Äî must be registered in PayOS dashboard

## Notifications
- Quiet hours: 22:00‚Äì06:50 VN time ‚Äî no notifications outside this window
- Exception: `morning_critical_655` type bypasses quiet hours ‚Äî only for `timing_critical = TRUE` conditions
- Max 2 notifications per user per day ‚Äî enforced in `dispatch.service.ts`
- Min gap between notifications: 4 hours
- iOS Safari: no OS-level web push ‚Äî use in-app banner via `GET /api/v1/notifications/pending` polling
- Push subscription stored in `push_subscriptions` table ‚Äî one active subscription per user per device

## Cron Jobs (Vietnam time)
- `protocol-adapt.ts`: 2am VN ‚Äî adaptive protocol switching after 10+ days no progress
- `pattern-detect.ts`: 3am VN ‚Äî pattern observation generation (14+ days data required)
- `email-sequence.ts`: every hour ‚Äî retention email dispatch
- `phase-gate-check.ts`: async after each check-in ‚Äî phase unlock evaluation
- `morning-critical-send.ts`: 06:50 daily ‚Äî timing_critical conditions only

## Protocol Rules
- Protocols are immutable (append-only) ‚Äî never UPDATE or DELETE protocol records
- When adapting protocol: create new protocol record with `version` incremented, set previous `is_current = FALSE`
- `createConditionWithPhaseGate()` must be called for every new condition ‚Äî never create condition without phase gate
- `filterProhibitedExercises()` must run before every protocol assignment ‚Äî frozen shoulder Phase 1 must never receive stretch exercises
